# Offline basemap data. The PMTiles archive is large (tens of MB to 1+ GB)
# and should be distributed via GitHub releases, not the git tree.
#
# To generate WebATM/static/tiles/world.pmtiles (the file the offline map
# style expects):
#
#   1. Install the pmtiles CLI:
#        # macOS / Linux with Go:
#        go install github.com/protomaps/go-pmtiles@latest
#        export PATH="$HOME/go/bin:$PATH"
#        ln -sf "$HOME/go/bin/go-pmtiles" "$HOME/go/bin/pmtiles"  # optional alias
#        # or grab a prebuilt binary from
#        #   https://github.com/protomaps/go-pmtiles/releases
#
#   2. Pick a daily planet build date from https://maps.protomaps.com/builds/
#      (e.g. 20260415) and extract just the zoom levels you need. Zoom 0-8
#      worldwide is ~400 MB - 1.2 GB and covers coastlines, major roads, and
#      country/state boundaries — enough context for ATM visualization:
#
#        mkdir -p WebATM/static/tiles
#        pmtiles extract \
#          https://build.protomaps.com/<YYYYMMDD>.pmtiles \
#          WebATM/static/tiles/world.pmtiles \
#          --maxzoom=8
#
#      To also include street-level detail for a specific region, re-run
#      extract with --bbox=<minLon,minLat,maxLon,maxLat> --maxzoom=12 into a
#      second file and add it as an extra source in offline-style.json.
#
#   3. Verify:      pmtiles show WebATM/static/tiles/world.pmtiles
#   4. In WebATM:   Settings -> Map Display Configuration -> Offline (Local PMTiles)
WebATM/static/tiles/*.pmtiles

WebATM/static/glyphs/*
WebATM/static/navdata/*

# Release tarballs built by script/build_release_tarball.sh and
# script/build_assets_tarball.sh at the repo root. These get uploaded to
# GitHub releases, never committed.
webatm-prebuilt-*.tar.gz
webatm-assets-*.tar.gz
